The paper deals with the problem of team grouping in social networks, which involves finding a grouping method that maximizes the total profit of the tasks that teams can complete while satisfying certain constraints. This problem is related to social networks (cs.SOC), optimization (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves finding an optimal solution. The paper also proposes a LP-based approximation algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.SI and cs.SOC, followed by cs.DS, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
